<emphasis box="[606,757,579,604]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Corydidarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[774,955,579,604]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[774,955,579,604]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Pseudoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1015,1161,579,604]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Trichoblattta</emphasis>
requires a clarification. Since Princis’ (1964) catalogue, Bey-Bienko (1969) and Anisyutkin (2003) described species under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure &amp; Zehntner" authorityYear="1895" box="[1290,1428,615,640]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Trichoblatta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1290,1428,615,640]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Trichoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whilst earlier taxonomists (
<bibRefCitation box="[454,614,651,675]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" refId="ref11454" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1893) Revision du systeme des Orthopteres et description des especes rapportees par M. Leonardo Fea de Birmanie. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, Series 2, 13, 5 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5121" type="journal article">Brunner 1893</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[624,787,650,675]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" refId="ref12226" refString="Shelford, R. (1907) On some new species of Blattidae in the Oxford and Paris Museums. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History Seventh Series, 19, 25 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930709487227" type="journal article">Shelford 1907</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[798,961,650,675]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" refId="ref11603" refString="Hanitsch, R. (1924) Blattidae collected by Prof. Gregory's expedition to Yunnan. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 20 (6), 337 - 338." type="journal article">Hanitsch 1924</bibRefCitation>
) described species under 
<taxonomicName box="[1248,1428,650,675]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1248,1428,650,675]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Pseudoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was not listed as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure &amp; Zehntner" authorityYear="1895" box="[584,723,686,711]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Trichoblatta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[584,723,686,711]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Trichoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[766,929,686,711]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" refId="ref11994" refString="Princis, K. (1964) Blattariae: Subordo Blaberoidea. Fam.: Panchloridae, Gynopeltididae, Derocalymmidae, Perisphaeriidae, Pycnoscelididae. In: Beier, M (Ed.), Orthopterorum Catalogus. Pars 6. Uitgeverij Dr. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage, pp. 175 - 281." type="journal article">Princis (1964)</bibRefCitation>
. These species should obviously be included in one genus, and these authors’ views of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure &amp; Zehntner" authorityYear="1895" box="[645,784,721,746]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Trichoblatta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[645,784,721,746]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Trichoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[845,1025,721,746]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[845,1025,721,746]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Pseudoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
overlap. We compared the original descriptions of these genera, and examined the photos of the 
<typeStatus box="[905,953,758,782]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">type</typeStatus>
specimens of the 
<typeStatus box="[1184,1232,758,782]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">type</typeStatus>
species, namely, 
<taxonomicName authority="Saussure" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1863" box="[151,512,792,817]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Perisphaeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glomeris">
<emphasis box="[151,403,792,817]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Perisphaeria glomeris</emphasis>
Saussure
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectionCode box="[549,634,793,816]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">MNHN</collectionCode>
(on loan from 
<collectionCode box="[808,896,793,817]" country="Switzerland" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/2jyg-xmd2" name="Museum d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">MHNG</collectionCode>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Saussure" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1863" box="[961,1304,792,817]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Perisphaeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis box="[961,1196,792,817]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Perisphaeria sericea</emphasis>
Saussure
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectionCode box="[1343,1433,793,817]" country="Switzerland" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/2jyg-xmd2" name="Museum d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">MHNG</collectionCode>
: they fall into one genus. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure &amp; Zehntner" authorityYear="1895" box="[565,704,828,853]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Trichoblatta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[565,704,828,853]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Trichoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is synonymized with 
<taxonomicName box="[959,1139,828,853]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[959,1139,828,853]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Pseudoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner" authorityYear="1865" box="[1278,1429,828,853]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Corydidarum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1429,828,853]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Corydidarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, now popular on the Internet, was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation box="[685,864,863,888]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" refId="ref11431" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1865) Nouveau Systeme des Blattaires. G. Braumuller, Vienna, 426 pp." type="book">Brunner (1865)</bibRefCitation>
. Leaving only a citation, 
<bibRefCitation box="[1156,1331,863,888]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" refId="ref11431" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1865) Nouveau Systeme des Blattaires. G. Braumuller, Vienna, 426 pp." type="book">Brunner (1865)</bibRefCitation>
assigned 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,302,899,924]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Corydidarum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,302,899,924]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Corydidarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authority="Saussure" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1863" box="[348,703,899,924]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Perisphaeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis box="[348,588,899,924]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Perisphaeria sericea</emphasis>
Saussure
</taxonomicName>
; thus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner" authorityYear="1865" box="[786,937,899,924]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Corydidarum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[786,937,899,924]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Corydidarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure &amp; Zehntner" authorityYear="1895" box="[1003,1142,899,924]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Trichoblatta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1003,1142,899,924]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Trichoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are objective synonyms. 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,328,934,959]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" refId="ref11431" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1865) Nouveau Systeme des Blattaires. G. Braumuller, Vienna, 426 pp." type="book">Brunner (1865)</bibRefCitation>
did not describe the genus, and no longer used this name in his subsequent works. The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,302,969,994]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Corydidarum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,302,969,994]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Corydidarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is absent from any other taxonomic works, i.e. it has never been formally used; therefore, it is undesired to use this name hereafter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1562]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1938" box="[199,327,1040,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Glomerexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,327,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Glomerexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[476,656,1040,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[476,656,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Pseudoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in apterous (Bey-Bienko 1938) or brachypterous male (
<bibRefCitation pageId="9" pageNumber="260" refId="ref12416" refString="Wang, Z. Q. &amp; Che, Y. L. (2011) Revision of the genus Glomerexis Bey-Bienko with description of one new species from China (Blattodea, Perisphaeriinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 137 (3 &amp; 4), 367 - 371." type="journal article">Wang &amp; Che 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Bey-Bienko (1938) distinguishes between these genera by wing-morph only, and did not suggest any other differences. However, wing-morph alone is insufficient for the generic diagnosis. The males of two brachypterous species
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li &amp; Wang &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Wang &amp; Wang" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[235,423,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="semisulcata" subSpecies="angustifolia">
, 
<emphasis box="[246,423,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Ps. angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hanitsch" authorityYear="1924" box="[479,654,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semisulcata">
<emphasis box="[479,654,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Ps. semisulcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which resemble the apterous 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1938" box="[999,1134,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Glomerexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibetana">
<emphasis box="[999,1134,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Ps. tibetana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differ from those of other 
<taxonomicName box="[151,332,1182,1207]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,332,1182,1207]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Pseudoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species: tiny ocellar spots and tiny typical carina lobe (like the females), and virga sclerite absent. We do not consider the former two differences to be of generic diagnosis, since these characters are also neoteny, and it is normal for the brachypterous males to exhibit neoteny, given that the apterous females are all neotenic. In comparison, the absence of virga sclerite can be a significant character that can be used to distinguish between genera, but we do not do so because no other significant differences can support the division. Nonetheless, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1938" box="[151,279,1359,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Glomerexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,279,1359,1384]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Glomerexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be regarded as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName box="[697,877,1359,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[697,877,1359,1384]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Pseudoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, if the male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1938" box="[1064,1201,1359,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Glomerexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibetana">
<emphasis box="[1064,1201,1359,1384]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Ps. tibetana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[1263,1311,1361,1385]" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1938" box="[151,279,1395,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Glomerexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,279,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Glomerexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, lacks the virga sclerite, too. This is likely true but requires an investigation. If the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Glomerexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibetana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Ps. tibetana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fall into the normal morphology of 
<taxonomicName box="[642,822,1430,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[642,822,1430,1455]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Pseudoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the contrary, a new subgenus should be established based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li &amp; Wang &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[264,444,1466,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis box="[264,444,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Ps. angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hanitsch" authorityYear="1924" box="[489,667,1466,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semisulcata">
<emphasis box="[489,667,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Ps. semisulcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Judging from current evidence, we synonymize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1938" box="[1247,1375,1466,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Glomerexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1247,1375,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Glomerexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[151,331,1501,1526]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Pseudoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="9" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,331,1501,1526]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="260">Pseudoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is premature to propose a subgenus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
